756x1094.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>无论你包含多少控制因素，你都不能排除还有其他第三种因素可以让人们结婚<em>并</em>让他们更快乐的可能性。也许是来自家人和朋友的某种社会支持，或者也许是遗传因素。谁知道！</p><p>但这说明了为什么我们需要<em>自然实验</em>。为了真正分离出婚姻和幸福之间的因果关系，我们需要政策、社会或经济条件等方面的某种随机变化，促使一些人在本来不会结婚的时候结婚，或者在本来不会结婚的时候不结婚。将有。这并不能<em>完全</em>回答这个问题，因为对不同的人或在不同的时间等仍然可能产生不同的影响。但它肯定会比我们现在的研究提供更清晰的答案。不幸的是，我找不到这样的自然实验，但也许存在。</p><p>无论如何，这是社会科学如此艰难的众多原因之一。</p><h4> 6.《星际迷航》再次伟大</h4><p>我一直是《星际迷航》的忠实粉丝。但在世纪之交之后，我注意到我对该系列所推出的内容的喜爱程度明显下降。我认为《企业》很生硬而且制作很差劲。我认为 J·J·艾布拉姆斯的电影还不错，但过于以动作为导向，而且有点翻版。我认为《发现号》是一次有趣且雄心勃勃的失败——试图将《星际迷航》带向全新的主题和叙事方向，但最终找不到任何有效的新方向。我认为《皮卡德》的前两季虽然值得一看，但感觉更像是帕特里克·斯图尔特的梦想序列的延伸。我已经接受了这样的想法：《星际迷航》和许多其他娱乐系列一样，刚刚失去了曾经让它与众不同的魔力。具有讽刺意味的是，最能捕捉这种魔力的节目是《奥维尔》，尽管其方式稍显业余，它最初的目的是模仿《星际迷航》。</p><p>然后，突然间，《星际迷航》又恢复正常了。不仅好，而且令人惊叹——在某些方面比以前更好。首先是卡通系列<a href="https://www.paramountplus.com/shows/star-trek-lower-decks/">《星际迷航：下层甲板》</a> ，这是一个模仿我们想象中的奥维尔号的系列。这是一种我没想到会很有趣的节目，但我感到惊喜。它绝对有《瑞克与莫蒂》的味道，这并不奇怪，因为创作者是《瑞克与莫蒂》的编剧和制片人。</p><p>与此同时，<a href="https://www.paramountplus.com/shows/star-trek-picard/">皮卡德</a>的第三季也是最后一季简直令人难以置信。它对《星际迷航：下一代》的作用就像原版电影在 70 年代和 80 年代对原版系列所做的那样，而 TNG 动作在 2000 年代从未成功做到过。它比 J·J·艾布拉姆斯的电影或探索频道更扣人心弦、更具电影感，但这些动作场面与情感和温柔的时刻交替出现，这是该系列几十年来一直未能解决的问题。是的，这是一次怀旧之旅，但这<em>不仅仅是</em>一次怀旧之旅，因为这些角色现在已经老了这一事实是该剧的基本组成部分。 （不用剧透太多，接近结尾时甚至有一个有趣的部分，当他们发现自己都老了时，变得非常有用。）最重要的是，皮卡德的结局在每个细节上都绝对是完美的，这使得《星际迷航》： 《下一代》是为数不多的拥有<em>两个</em>完美结局的电视节目之一。</p><p>但《星际迷航》新时代最精彩的部分是<a href="https://www.paramountplus.com/shows/star-trek-strange-new-worlds/">《奇异新世界》</a> 。对于那些不知道的人来说，这个系列是探索号的衍生品，也是原始系列的前传——它发生在柯克和史波克成名的最初的企业号上，五年前柯克就任船长。该剧由原剧组的 Spock 和 Uhura 主演，还有一些在原剧中扮演小角色的角色——派克船长、查普尔护士、M&#39;Benga 医生和 Una Chin-Riley（《数字》）。一”）。还有一些新角色，柯克和原系列剧组的其他成员偶尔也会客串。</p><p>这个节目太棒了。</p><p> Most reviewers talk about how the series is a return to the basic Star Trek pattern — themes of optimism and exploration, a highly competent crew who are all basically good people and who tend to make reasonable judgement calls under pressure, an episodic story structure, and Klingons who don&#39;t look like weird lizard-creatures. And that is all true. But SNW is not a nostalgia trip in any way — it&#39;s more like a modern update on the original series concept, similar to what TNG did. It leverages the skill of modern “prestige TV writers” to insert emotional drama into the Star Trek framework without the lazy expedients of making the characters do stupid stuff or act like jerks. The bridge crew represent the best of humanity; they sob in their rooms, tell each other small lies, and have awkward romances, while still being hyper-competent at their jobs. The structure is episodic, but the “space monster of the week” plots are just a wrapper around a whole lot of slow-burning character-focused story arcs.</p><p> Instead of being yet another Game of Thrones wannabe, in other words, Strange New Worlds represents an evolution beyond the now-familiar 2010s format — a blend of episodic and long-term stories that feels like something fundamentally <em>new</em> . And that blend also allows SNW to constantly experiment — there&#39;s one episode that&#39;s a musical (don&#39;t worry, it&#39;s good), and one that&#39;s a semi-cartoon crossover with Lower Decks. I can&#39;t remember a time when I was this excited to see a TV show every week, and a large part of that is that I don&#39;t know what to expect.</p><p> It also has one of the best <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OS2VhlkFmRQ">opening sequences</a> of any Star Trek show ever, if not <em>the</em> best.</p><p> Strange New Worlds is simply the best new Star Trek show since Deep Space Nine, and it&#39;s among the best things you can watch on TV right now. Audiences are realizing it too, as the show <a href="https://trekmovie.com/2023/07/20/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-hits-streaming-top-10-again-pushes-paramount-to-new-milestone/">gains</a> in<a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/star-trek-strange-new-worlds-cbs-1235573914/">popularity</a> . When people point at this show and say “Star Trek is back”, they aren&#39;t kidding. The writers&#39; and actors&#39; strikes will interrupt the regular release of SNW seasons (Note to studios: Just pay the damn writers and actors, please!), but in the meantime there are 20 episodes to watch, so <a href="https://www.paramountplus.com/shows/star-trek-strange-new-worlds/">check them out</a> . </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>Subscribe now</span></a> </p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-6bf?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-6bf?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>Share</span></a> </p><div id="youtube2-OZ2u8747v_8" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;OZ2u8747v_8&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/OZ2u8747v_8?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp